{"id":78749,"title":"Allergic rhinitis: Diagnosis through management.","abstract":"Allergic rhinitis (AR) is an immune hypersensitivity response of the nasal mucosa affecting children and adults. Patients with a genetic predisposition become sensitized to certain allergens over time with repeated exposures. This article will discuss AR from diagnosis through treatment.","date":"2014-03-17","categories":"Otorhinolaryngologic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24584167","annotations":[{"name":"Allergic rhinitis","weight":0.844161,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergic_rhinitis"},{"name":"Human nose","weight":0.759949,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_nose"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.751095,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Mucous membrane","weight":0.745929,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mucous_membrane"},{"name":"Allergy","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergy"},{"name":"Allergen","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergen"},{"name":"Hypersensitivity","weight":0.684152,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypersensitivity"},{"name":"Mucus","weight":0.681913,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mucus"},{"name":"Rhinitis","weight":0.618362,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhinitis"},{"name":"Genetics","weight":0.591177,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetics"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.547908,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Immunity (medical)","weight":0.468442,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunity_(medical)"},{"name":"Genetic predisposition","weight":0.113053,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetic_predisposition"},{"name":"Arkansas","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arkansas"},{"name":"Exposu